idized linoleic acids are detectable in the oral cavity of humans with minimal input from the olfactory, capsaicin, and viscosity-assessing tactile systems.},
author = {Chale-Rush, Angela and Burgess, John R and Mattes, Richard D},
doi = {10.1093/chemse/bjm007},
file = {:C$\backslash$:/Users/Michael/Documents/Grad School/research/references/Chale-Rush-Evidence for human orosensory taste sensitivity to free fatty acids.pdf:pdf},
